I had a week long event this week at the InterContinental and &quot;lived through&quot; the heavy rains at the first of the week.  From our General Session Ballroom we could watch the water bubbling up through the manhole covers and running down the street maybe 6&quot;-10&quot; deep.  Heard that most schools were closed for just one day (a few for two).  It didn't dampen the spirits of our attendees, though we did have a few who had to iron their clothes dry when they were caught by surprise by the rain.  (I am from Oregon.  I only notice rain when it is ankle deep.)

By the way, if you have any fears about holding an event in New Orleans, loose them.  Everyone we worked with were very appreciative that we were there.  Our conference was for about 200 people, mostly from the US and everyone enjoyed the conference, the hotel and the city.

